Summaries

Five sample summaries

[1] Speaker’s father had gone to Australia to talk about the election. There were many people who had different ideas and backgrounds. However, He talked with them with a big smile. Then she recognized that his conversation was constructive. To understand how we go interconversion, not looking for the victory, but the progress. The first stage of that was choosing curiously over clash. Not just from the conversation, but even the relationship sometimes makes people shut down. Depending on the tense cannot be said to be a good conversation. The whole point of the curious conversation is to understand the other person’s perspective, and to see on the other side. Then we just need only one question and one answer. If we think that others should have the same opinions, we will not be ab;t to progress. Constructive conversation is like a climbing wall, to repeatedly attack our opinions and accept others' one, and then attack again. Through challenges, we can expect that our ideas will get better.
[2]                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           
[3] Julia Dhar’s father went to the United States to talk to hundreds of people about the election and hear their options. He had constructive conversations, and by the end of each talk, the person who interviewed was smiling. This shows something important: choosing curiosity over conflict. Instead of being negative about someone’s views, we should accept them first and ask why they think that way. It is also important to improve our own perspective by considering the other person’s opposing opinions.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   
[4] The speaker talks about how his father went to America in 2016 to have conversations with people about the election. His goal wasn’t just to talk about politics, but to listen and understand different views. Despite differences in opinions, everyone walked away from the conversations feeling positive. The speaker explains that in order to have a constructive conversation, we need to focus on curiosity instead of trying to win the argument. He suggests asking questions like, “What can you share to help me see your point of view?” This helps people feel heard and can lead to a more meaningful conversation. He also talks about the importance of having a clear purpose in a discussion, and how focusing on common goals can help bridge divides. In the end, the speaker believes that by choosing curiosity, expecting growth from conversations, and finding a shared purpose, we can improve our communication and move forward together.                                                                   
[5] The speaker’s father wanted to talk with people about the election, but he didn’t want to discuss issues, just wanted to understand others. The speaker, who experienced the debate competition, said her father was doing “constructive conversation”. These days, we have a lot of ways to communicate but in reality, we are divided into many fields. Also, people cannot trust others because of changing beliefs. The first way to start “constructive conversation”, is to present our curiosity. Most people think that we need to crush others for discussing, but according to the speaker, the most important thing is understanding the others’ position and getting the opponent interested in me. When our opinion is criticized, we should explain about that each time. Second, we should have a clear goal or purpose of discussion. To set the purpose, we need to speak from a holistic perspective. To build a good relationship, the conversation must be conducted with curiosity and care.

Opinions

five sample opinions

[1] I think that constructive conversation is difficult if the person who I talk to isn’t conscious of it. That is because if I try to have a curious conversation, but the person doesn’t try it, it will not become constructive conversation. I think good conversation will not continue. But, I think avoiding a crash and having a curious conversation is important, because I'll be able to know the person deeply. I think curiosity conversation has an attitude of knowing the person, so it is needed in real life. Surely, in formal debate, it is required to clash, but in common conversation, I think we should not clash.                                                                                         
[2] I was surprised that there are specific ways of having good conversations. The speaker raised her experiences about her father and the person who was her boss, the deputy prime minister of New Zealand. These experiences explain the reality of her opinion. I especially agree with the speaker's opinion that if we have the same purpose through the conversation, people tend to have big and good relationships. For example, when I was in junior high school, I was a member of the girl’s basketball team. There are twenty teammates, but we have very good relationships. It is because we have a purpose to win the match. Everyone would like to win in the basketball game, so a little crash was not a problem.
[3] After listening to this Ted Talk, I wonder how nicer the society might be if her attitude for conversation applied to the Japanese political scene. Recent political discussion in the Japanese congress is meaningless because many politicians just focus on kicking other politicians out of them, so that their opinions are empty. I can’t understand why they don’t try to make nicer and brilliant ideas or speeches to change Japan. I think that they should learn from her attitude of conversations and make attractive ideas for both other politicians and citizens that might be picked up more easily in the Japanese congress or elections.                                                                     
[4] I want to talk better. I often think it would be good if I had not said it. In addition, I want to talk well and improve my communication skills. So, I am interested in this video. However, I usually attack different opinions. I think I want to protect my opinion. If I attack different opinions, I cannot take new ideas into my brain. I should improve this situation and I want to enjoy communication.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
[5] I always don’t know if my opinion is right when I argue. So I can’t argue much. However, I can understand the point of the discussion in this video, and I want to use it. In today’s world, there are many discussions about environmental problems, gender issues, and so on. I think that constructive conversation plays an important role in solving these problems. Constructive conservation should be attracted a lot of attention worldwide.
